# ImpactConnect: Data-Driven Volunteer Coordination

ImpactConnect is a powerful, premium web platform designed for NGOs and local social groups to digitize fragmented community needs and intelligently match them with available volunteers.

![Project Preview](https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1531482615713-2afd69097998?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1000)

## 🚀 Overview
Local NGOs often struggle with "scattered" data trapped in paper surveys. ImpactConnect centralizes this information, providing a real-time dashboard of community needs and a **Smart Matching Engine** to optimize resource allocation.

## ✨ Key Features
- **Smart Matcher Engine:** Algorithm-driven volunteer allocation based on skill overlap, proximity, and availability.
- **Infrastructure Management:** Real-time occupancy and status tracking for shelters, clinics, and community centers.
- **Impact Analytics:** Dynamic CSS-based charts visualizing community need trends and resolution rates.
- **Data Ingestion:** Streamlined forms to digitize field reports and paper surveys instantly.
- **Premium Design:** A modern, high-performance UI built with Glassmorphism, CSS Variables, and zero external frameworks.

## 🛠️ Technology Stack
- **Structure:** Semantic HTML5
- **Logic:** Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+)
- **Styling:** Modern CSS3 (CSS Variables, Flexbox, Grid, Backdrop-filter)
- **Icons:** Google Material Symbols

## 📂 Project Structure
```text
├── index.html          # Main internal dashboard
├── landing.html        # Public-facing marketing page
├── css/
│   ├── style.css       # Dashboard and core app styling
│   └── landing.css     # Landing page specific styling
└── js/
    ├── app.js          # Core application logic & view routing
    ├── matchingEngine.js # Scoring algorithm for volunteer matching
    └── mockData.js     # Simulated community data
```

## 🚦 Getting Started
No installation or dependencies required.
1. Clone the repository.
2. Open `landing.html` in any modern web browser to view the public site.
3. Navigate to `index.html` (or click "Go to Dashboard" from the landing page) to access the coordinator tools.

